SIMPLE: chinch
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chinch
<hw>Chinch</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. Sp.
<ets>chinche</ets>, fr. L. <er>cimex</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The bedbug (<spn>Cimex
lectularius</spn>).</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A bug (<spn>Blissus
leucopterus</spn>), which, in the United States, is very destructive to
grass, wheat, and other grains; -- also called
<altname>chiniz</altname>, <altname>chinch bug</altname>, <altname>chink
bug</altname>. It resembles the bedbug in its disgusting odor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chincha</ent>⟦br⟧
